🚧 Smart Manhole Monitoring System

IoT and GSM-based embedded system for real-time underground manhole hazard monitoring with automated SMS alerts.

📌 Overview

The Smart Manhole Monitoring System is an Arduino Mega + SIM900 based embedded safety solution designed to detect hazardous conditions inside underground manholes.

The system continuously monitors:

💨 Toxic Gas Leakage

🌡 High Temperature

🔥 Fire Presence

💧 Water Level Rise

📳 Vibration / Unauthorized Activity

If any parameter crosses a predefined threshold, the system:

Displays alert on LCD

Sends real-time SMS notification via GSM module

Prevents repeated SMS spamming using alert flags

This project is designed for smart city infrastructure, municipal safety, and industrial monitoring applications.

🛠 Hardware Components Used
8

Arduino Mega 2560

SIM900 GSM Module

MQ2 Gas Sensor

LM35 Temperature Sensor

Flame Sensor Module

Water Level Sensor

SW-420 Vibration Sensor

16x2 LCD Display

Jumper Wires

External Power Supply

⚙️ System Working

Sensors continuously collect environmental data.

Arduino reads analog and digital values.

Values are compared against defined safety thresholds.

If limit exceeds:

LCD displays warning.

SMS alert is sent using AT commands.

Alert flags ensure single SMS per event.

When value returns to normal, alert resets.

📊 Threshold Configuration
Parameter	Threshold
Gas Level	> 200
Temperature	> 35°C
Flame Level	> 150
Water Level	> 500
Vibration	HIGH
📲 GSM Communication

The SIM900 GSM module operates in AT Command Text Mode.

Example Commands:

AT+CMGF=1
AT+CMGS="PhoneNumber"
Message Content
CTRL+Z

Example Alerts Sent:

ALERT! Gas Level High in Manhole!

ALERT! Fire Detected in Manhole!

ALERT! Water Level High in Manhole!

ALERT! Temperature High in Manhole!

ALERT! Vibration Detected in Manhole!

🔌 Pin Configuration
📍 Sensors
Sensor	Arduino Pin
MQ2 Gas Sensor	A0
LM35 Temperature	A1
Flame Sensor	A2
Water Sensor	A3
Vibration Sensor	23
📍 LCD (16x2)
LCD Pin	Arduino Pin
RS	7
EN	6
D4	5
D5	4
D6	3
D7	2
📍 GSM Module
SIM900	Arduino Mega
TX	RX1
RX	TX1
GND	GND
